narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I think it helped me visualize surface and objects in 3D better.
Applications of integrals and derivatives such as Line integrals, and surface integrals.
I became much more comfortable with the idea of integration in higher dimensions - from partials to integration theorems.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The way that this course is structured with pre class quizzes and basically going over what we watched in the quizzes in class is such a waste of time. The math department at Yale is faulty, and this course is evident of it. This course moves way too fast, it should be slowed down more. There would be times when we learn more than three to four new topics per week. It's hard to actually understand the content when the course moves at such a high speed. There aren't really any strengths that I can think of.
The course is very fast at times and can be difficult to keep up.

Strengths: well-organized, lots of resources and sufficient support from TAs. 
Weaknesses: Be prepared to spend a lot of time on psets. I wish they were weighted heavier on the final grade.
The course doesn't move that fast and the psets are good practice for the exams which aren't too difficult.

Strengths: challenging but engaging mathematical concepts
Weaknesses: limited resources for revision, particularly in preparation for exams

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: No, avoid this course if you do not need to take it.
Maybe, it can be useful for higher level economics and mathematics but I definitely wouldn't take it for fun.

I would recommend this course to another student. Although calculus has a reputation for being a drag - and it can be if you make it out to be - I believe that I greatly enhanced my critical thinking skills and general mathematic inventory.
If interested yes. The course is actually not too hard and the topics are very useful in other classes.
Yes - its a great course for anyone interested in going further with the physical sciences.
